Last note, VOLUME. Trade VOLUME. Focus on REAL trends, real VOLUME. Liquidity is what it's all about.
Sometimes best trade is no trade if unfamiliar. For me, I have about 20 names I love at night and 3-5 FOCUS names in the AM.
Never know what tomorrow brings. Treat each day as a new. Never say "eh it's OK because yesterday was good" WRONG process.
There are long opportunities & short opportunities galore right now. Be PATIENT wait for ENTRIES & scale if RIGHT not WRONG. Best of Luck.
You never know where/what opportunities are ahead so let's not let these days pass w/o proper action. Make changes tomorrow!
First step is YOU. This is an UNREAL time and if you're NOT capitalizing on it take a step back REVIEW your trades IMMEDIATELY.
If you have trouble trading out of gate REALIZE it stop blowing your wad in the first 3 minutes. WAIT, join trends 945-10AM+ scale if right.
Once on right side of a few names you can downsize and let them work for you while focused on other names.
Use this time to make GOOD decisions. Moves many times are through entire day. Focus on getting on RIGHT side not fighting the wrong side.
When trades aren't working many traders stick with it and "see what they'll do" there is no time for that in this market with some much opp
If you stay with trades that are not working not only are you wasting capital, you're wasting mental capital that could be focused elsewhere
The market is incredibly forgiving right now, if you make a few mistakes there's a dozen more opportunities coming right around the corner.
I've made many mistakes & have many losers but in this market it's about cutting those and adding to winners and letting them work.
You never know how long opportunities like this will last, when they are here you need to capitalize on them.
This is the time to make smart choices and bulk up your trading accounts. Focus on joining not fighting trends. Follow the money.
This market is absolutely incredible. If you are having difficulty it's time to look at the process, adapt, and make changes that work.
